                   On Demand   
                


Did you know that over 160 million records have been compromised just from breaches at enterprises like Sony, Anthem, Premera, Nieman Marcus, Target, and Home Depot? Or, that every second, 12 people become a victim of cybercrime? Though staggering, it shouldn’t be a shock. Cybercrime has grown significantly in volume and in sophistication, and everyone from customers to IT professionals to executives are being adversely affected. So what are technology providers doing to protect enterprise customers like you? How are they proactively combatting cybercrime?
Join speakers, Pete Boden, General Manager of Cloud and Enterprise Security, and Richard Boscovich, Senior Attorney at the Digital Crimes Unit, for our webinar, The Emerging Era of Cyber Defense and Cybercrime: How Microsoft Helps Keep Customers and Data Safe. Register now to learn some of the best practices Microsoft employs across cybercrime, cybersecurity, and cyber defense to help keep our customer’s safe and to help protect online consumers worldwide. In this webinar, you will learn:

How the Microsoft Cyber Defense Operations Center teams protect, detect, and respond to threats on our platform
How the Microsoft Digital Crimes Unit serves to fight malware, reduce digital risk, and protect vulnerable populations 
How Microsoft uses the intelligence gained from these operations to help improve security for our customers

We look forward to you joining us.





Pete Boden
General Manager of Cloud and Enterprise Security



 Richard Boscovich
Senior Attorney at the Digital Crimes Unit

























